LorebookItems.value:
Avi or "The Avi" squats like a rusted behemoth on the wasteland horizon. Its neon sign, a flickering echo of pre-war extravagance, barely spells out "Avi." This ramshackle saloon, built from the decaying bones of the once-luxurious Avi Resort and Casino, is a beacon for the down-and-out of the wasteland. Inside, the air hangs heavy with the smell of stale brahmin hide, cheap liquor, and desperation. Flickering neon casts an eerie glow on the faded slot machines and threadbare remnants of casino carpeting. The upper floors of the casino are dedicated to the offices of the town mayor, "Major" Marlo McBride, his staff, and his guards.
"Reginald 'Reg' Montgomery":{"hair":"slicked_back","wears":"three_piece_suit","job":"wasteland_gambler","gender":"male","smooth_talking","selfish"},
"Lila 'Lucky' Laveau":{"hair":"long_black","wears":"colorful_headscarf","job":"wasteland_performer","gender":"female","charming","manipulative"}

The stench of brahmin dung mingles with the oily tang of scavenged scrap in the repurposed Sun Valley-Bison Airport control tower. Faded air traffic control screens now blare bartering offers in garish colors, while flickering neon signs cast an unforgiving glare on the salvaged wares piled high - a chaotic marketplace overflowing with the detritus of a lost civilization.
"Gizmo":{"hair":"brown_ponytail","wears":"tattered_leather_jacket","job":"ex-brotherhood_scribe","gender":"female","resourceful"},
"August 'Augie' Adams":{"hair":"shaggy_brown","wears":"thick_glasses","job":"wasteland_scientist","gender":"male","manic_genius"}}

Beneath the relentless sun, the former Mesquite Creek area is a symphony of rust. Skeletal remains of pre-war vehicles litter the dusty landscape, each twisted chassis a monument to forgotten journeys and the relentless march of time. Rusty Rhodes presides over this kingdom of twisted metal, her gruff voice a lone melody amidst the creak of scavenged tools and the clang of salvaged parts being bartered.
"Ruby Rhoades":{"hair":"long_red","wears":"salvaged_pre-war_clothing","job":"wasteland_trader","gender":"female","charismatic"},
"Gizmo":{"hair":"brown_ponytail","wears":"tattered_leather_jacket","job":"ex-brotherhood_scribe","gender":"female","resourceful"}

Sandbags line the heavily fortified walls of the Sun Valley-Bison Airport, a stark contrast to the faded travel posters clinging to the peeling paint. Inside, repurposed barracks reek of stale air and gun oil, the rhythmic click of boots on concrete echoing through the halls like a metronome keeping time with the ever-present threat. Dim lighting hangs over crudely assembled desks laden with weapons and ammo, a constant reminder of the iron grip the NCR maintains on this corner of the wasteland.
"Ranger Duncan Slade":{"hair":"under_stetson","wears":"worn_leather_duster_faded_NCR_uniform","job":"sheriff","gender":"male","loyal"},
"AX-101 'Axee'":{"hair":"none","wears":"metal_plating","job":"wasteland_hunter","gender":"female","craves_attention","easily_bored"}

Sun-bleached flags, once vibrant pre-war tournament boasts, hang limp. Their frayed edges flutter like wounded birds against the relentless desert wind. A faint, sweet decay mingles with the metallic tang of disinfectant, a constant reminder amidst the wreckage. Jagged teeth of emerald green, remnants of meticulously manicured greens, pierce cracked concrete. Harsh light from scavenged lamps throws grotesque shadows across makeshift tables littered with gleaming instruments. Low murmurs and the rhythmic hiss of a sprayer weave a counterpoint to the mournful song of the wind whistling through shattered windows. A single, crisp bandage lies stark white against a rusty wrench.
"Dr. Morgan Tilly":{"hair":"brown","wears":"worn_scrubs_medical_bag","job":"wasteland_doctor","gender":"female","gentle"},
"Dr. Anya Petrova":{"hair":"short_black","wears":"dirty_lab_coat_advanced_Pip-Boy","job":"vault_dweller_scientist","gender":"female","brilliant_neurotic"}

